He is  Australia's most notorious and well recognised criminal, but Ned Kelly may never have even existed if it weren't for his father stealing two pigs more than 170 years ago.

Public records published on Findmypast.com on Friday trace Ned Kelly's path from before his father John Kelly  became a criminal in Ireland to years later when he would eventually do the same in Australia.

Prison transfer records show John Kelly, also known as Red, was arrested for stealing two pigs back in 1841 and sent to Australia as a convict. 

